  "texts": [
    "Guided by evidence that coarse structure emerges before fine-grained semantics in diffusion [20,41], we design ISAC as a hierarchical, instance-first, training-free guidance.",
    "Figure 4 illustrates how Phase 1 (Sec.",
    "3.2) shapes class-agnostic instance layouts from self-attention and how Phase 2 (Sec.",
    "3.3) aligns semantic evidence to these layouts, yielding instance-aware semantics that prevent cross-instance mixing.",
    "BackgroundText-to-image diffusion models Diffusion models learn to reverse a forward noising process that gradually corrupts a sample X 0 into noise X T, conditioned on a text embedding T ∈ R L×d."
  ]
}